    sections: [
      { h: 'The Rise of International Esports Travel', body: `The global esports industry has exploded in scale and ambition. Major tournaments like The International (Dota 2), League of Legends World Championship, CS2 Majors, and Valorant Champions now draw teams from dozens of countries to compete for prize pools in the tens of millions of dollars.\n\nFor professional players, coaches, analysts, and content creators, international travel is now as routine as it is for traditional athletes. And like any traveling professional, staying connected is essential for performance, communication, and content creation.` },
      { h: 'Why Connectivity Matters for Esports Professionals', body: `**Team communication:** Modern esports teams use Discord, Slack, and proprietary tools for real-time communication during training sessions and tournament preparation. Reliable, low-latency internet is non-negotiable.\n\n**Scrimmages and online preparation:** Even during tournament travel, teams continue online practice. This requires a stable, fast connection — hotel Wi-Fi often doesn\'t cut it.\n\n**Content creation:** Streamers and content creators traveling with teams capture behind-the-scenes content for YouTube, Twitch, and TikTok. Uploading large video files requires high-speed mobile data.\n\n**Tournament registration and check-in:** Event platforms, ticketing systems, and communication with organizers all require reliable internet access.` },
      { h: 'eSIM: The Esports Traveler\'s Best Tool', body: `Traditional options for international connectivity (roaming plans, local SIM cards) are expensive, time-consuming to set up, or both. eSIM technology offers a clean solution:\n\n• **No physical SIM required:** Teams don\'t waste time hunting for SIM card shops in unfamiliar cities.\n• **Instant activation:** Buy a plan online, scan the QR code, connect immediately.\n• **Multiple plans:** eSIM-capable phones can store multiple profiles. Keep your home carrier active for calls, use WoWo SIM for data.\n• **Cost-effective:** Flat-rate data plans are far cheaper than roaming on home carrier plans.` },
      { h: 'Best Destinations for Esports Events in 2026', body: `**South Korea (Seoul):** The spiritual home of esports, with world-class venues, outstanding 5G coverage, and a gaming culture unlike anywhere else. WoWo SIM Korea plans ensure you stay connected throughout.\n\n**United States:** Major events in cities including New York, Dallas, Chicago, and Los Angeles. Strong 4G/5G infrastructure nationwide.\n\n**Germany (Cologne, Berlin):** Europe\'s esports hub. IEM Cologne, ESL One, and Dreamhack events draw global audiences.\n\n**Japan (Tokyo):** Growing rapidly as an esports destination with excellent infrastructure and world-class connectivity.` },
