      { h: 'Why Use an eSIM in Turkey?', body: `Turkey is an extraordinary destination spanning two continents, with Istanbul\'s incredible history, Cappadocia\'s surreal landscapes, the turquoise coast, and the ruins of ancient civilizations. Staying connected helps you navigate Istanbul\'s maze-like bazaars, translate menus in local restaurants, and share those hot air balloon sunrise photos over Göreme in real time.\n\nTurkey has excellent 4G LTE coverage in cities and tourist areas, with 5G rolling out in major urban centers. The question is how to get connected affordably as a foreign visitor.` },
      { h: 'WoWo SIM Turkey Plans', body: `WoWo SIM offers Turkey-specific eSIM plans starting from $4.50, connecting to top Turkish networks for reliable coverage across the country.\n\n**1GB / 7 days** — from $4.50 — For short city breaks in Istanbul or Ankara\n**3GB / 15 days** — from $9.00 — For a week-long trip including coastal towns\n**5GB / 30 days** — from $14.00 — For longer explorations including Cappadocia, Ephesus, and the coast\n**10GB / 30 days** — for extended stays or digital nomads\n\nAll plans provide 4G LTE connectivity. No registration with Turkish authorities required (unlike local SIM cards purchased in Turkey).` },
      { h: 'The Local SIM Registration Problem', body: `If you buy a local Turkish SIM card, there\'s an important complication: foreign phone numbers must be registered with the Turkish telecommunications authority (BTK) within 120 days, or the SIM will be locked to Turkey-only calling. This registration fee costs around $50 USD.\n\nFor tourists on short visits, this is an absurd bureaucratic hurdle. An eSIM completely bypasses this requirement — there\'s no local registration needed. This is one of the strongest arguments for using WoWo SIM in Turkey rather than a local SIM.` },
