      { h: 'Thailand Connectivity Overview', body: `Thailand consistently ranks among Southeast Asia\'s best-connected countries for travelers. 4G LTE coverage is excellent in Bangkok, Chiang Mai, Phuket, Koh Samui, and other tourist hubs. 5G has launched in Bangkok and is expanding to major cities.\n\nRural areas, islands, and national parks have varying connectivity. Remote islands like Koh Tao have basic coverage; popular ones like Koh Phi Phi and Koh Samui have strong 4G.` },
      { h: 'eSIM vs Local SIM in Thailand', body: `**WoWo SIM Thailand eSIM (recommended for most travelers):**\n\n• Buy before you travel — QR code in your email within seconds\n• Activate automatically on arrival at Suvarnabhumi or Don Mueang airports\n• Plans from $3.50 connecting to DTAC, True Move H, or AIS networks\n• No language barrier, no airport queues\n• Keep your home number active for calls/SMS\n\n**Local Tourist SIMs:**\n\n• Available at airport counters from AIS (recommended), TrueMove H, and DTAC\n• Good value for longer stays (7-day unlimited data from around 300 THB / $8)\n• Require passport registration at purchase\n• Need to return and replace when you move on to the next country` },
