  'global-connectivity-digital-nomads-2026': {
    title: 'Global Connectivity for Digital Nomads: The Complete 2026 Guide',
    category: 'Informative', date: 'Mar 9, 2026', emoji: '💻',
    readTime: '9 min read',
    desc: 'The complete guide to staying connected as a digital nomad in 2026.',
    sections: [
      { h: 'The Digital Nomad Reality in 2026', body: `An estimated 40 million people globally now identify as digital nomads — location-independent workers who leverage technology to work from anywhere. From developers and designers to content creators and consultants, more professionals than ever are working while exploring the world.\n\nThe single biggest challenge? Reliable internet. Hotels offer Wi-Fi that drops during video calls. Cafes have shared connections that crawl during peak hours. Co-working spaces are the gold standard but not everywhere.\n\nThe smart solution is a combination: a reliable eSIM for mobile data backup, and targeted use of co-working spaces and hotel connections for heavy-bandwidth work.` },
