  'what-is-esim-how-does-it-work': {
    title: 'What is an eSIM and How Does It Work?',
    category: 'Informative', date: 'Mar 9, 2026', emoji: '📱',
    readTime: '7 min read',
    desc: 'A complete beginner\'s guide to understanding eSIM technology — what it is, how to install one, and why travelers love it.',
    sections: [
      { h: 'What is an eSIM?', body: `An eSIM (embedded SIM) is a digital version of the traditional SIM card built directly into your device. While a physical SIM is a small removable chip you insert into your phone, an eSIM is soldered into the phone\'s motherboard during manufacturing. It cannot be removed.\n\nInstead of inserting a physical card to activate a mobile plan, you download a "profile" from a carrier wirelessly, typically by scanning a QR code. This profile contains all the information the eSIM needs to connect to that carrier\'s network.\n\nSince 2018, major smartphone manufacturers including Apple, Samsung, and Google have included eSIM capabilities in their flagship devices. Today, most phones released from 2020 onwards support eSIM.` },
      { h: 'How is eSIM Different from a Physical SIM?', body: `**Physical SIM:**\n• Removable chip that slots into your phone\n• Tied to one carrier at a time (unless dual-SIM)\n• Must be physically replaced to switch carriers\n• Can be lost or damaged\n• Requires visiting a store or waiting for mail delivery\n\n**eSIM:**\n• Built into the phone, cannot be removed or lost\n• Can store multiple carrier profiles simultaneously\n• Switch between carriers/plans instantly via settings\n• Activated wirelessly by scanning a QR code\n• Works across international carriers — perfect for travel\n\nThe practical result: you can have your home carrier on eSIM profile 1 (for calls and SMS from family) and a WoWo SIM travel plan on eSIM profile 2 (for cheap international data).` },
      { h: 'Step-by-Step: How to Install a WoWo SIM eSIM', body: `**Step 1 — Purchase your plan:**\nVisit WoWoSIM.com, select your destination and data plan, and complete checkout. Payment takes seconds.\n\n**Step 2 — Receive your QR code:**\nWithin seconds of purchase, you\'ll receive an email containing your eSIM QR code and installation instructions.\n\n**Step 3 — Open your phone settings:**\n• iPhone: Settings → Mobile Data → Add eSIM\n• Android (Samsung): Settings → Connections → SIM Manager → Add mobile plan\n• Android (Google Pixel): Settings → Network & Internet → SIMs → Add a SIM\n\n**Step 4 — Scan the QR code:**\nPoint your phone\'s camera at the QR code on screen or printed email. Your phone downloads and installs the eSIM profile automatically.\n\n**Step 5 — Set data preferences:**\nChoose which line (home SIM or WoWo SIM) to use for data. Select WoWo SIM for data while keeping your home SIM for calls and SMS.` },
      { h: 'Which Devices Support eSIM?', body: `**Apple:**\niPhone XR, XS, XS Max (2018) and all newer iPhones through the iPhone 17 series support eSIM. iPhone 14 and later (US models) are eSIM-only with no physical SIM tray.\n\niPad Pro (3rd generation+), iPad Air (3rd generation+), iPad mini (5th generation+), and iPad (7th generation+) with cellular also support eSIM.\n\n**Samsung:**\nGalaxy S20 series and newer, Galaxy Z Fold 3+, Galaxy Z Flip 3+, Galaxy Note 20+, and many recent Galaxy A series devices.\n\n**Google:**\nPixel 3 and all newer Pixel devices through Pixel 9 series.\n\n**Other Android:**\nMotorola Razr 2019+, select OnePlus, Xiaomi, OPPO, and Huawei models.\n\n**To check:** Go to Settings → About Phone (Android) or Settings → General → About (iPhone) and look for "EID" — if present, your device supports eSIM.` },
      { h: 'Common eSIM Questions', body: `**Q: Can I use two phone numbers at once?**\nYes! With dual-SIM/dual-eSIM phones, you can keep your home number active for calls and SMS while using WoWo SIM for data simultaneously.\n\n**Q: What happens if I run out of data?**\nYou\'ll receive a notification. Simply buy a new WoWo SIM plan from your dashboard — it activates within seconds.\n\n**Q: Can I reuse my eSIM QR code?**\nNo — each QR code is single-use. Once scanned and installed, the QR code is consumed. Keep your account login details to manage and reorder plans.\n\n**Q: Will eSIM work if my phone is locked to a carrier?**\nPotentially not. Check if your phone is unlocked (works with any carrier) before purchasing an eSIM from a different carrier. Contact your home carrier to unlock your phone if needed.` },
    ],
    related: ['best-esim-europe-2026', 'best-esim-international-travel-2026'],
    cta_dest: '/',
    cta_text: 'Browse All eSIM Plans',
  },

  'best-esim-international-travel-2026': {
    title: 'Best eSIM for International Travel in 2026 – Complete Guide for Travelers',
