      { h: 'Why eSIM Has Become the Standard for Travelers', body: `Five years ago, eSIM was a niche technology understood only by tech enthusiasts. In 2026, it\'s the standard for international travelers. Apple\'s iPhone 14 (US models) shipped without a physical SIM tray at all — a bold statement that eSIM is the future.\n\nThe reason travelers love eSIM is simple: it eliminates the most frustrating aspects of international travel connectivity. No more hunting for SIM card shops in unfamiliar airports. No more paying absurd roaming fees. No more carrying multiple physical SIM cards and remembering which slot you put which one in.` },
