      { h: 'WoWo SIM: Our Recommendation', body: `After extensive testing across 30+ countries, WoWo SIM delivers on the metrics that matter most for travelers:\n\n**Coverage:** 195+ countries, including regional plans for Europe (30+ countries), Asia Pacific (20+ countries), and global plans for frequent multi-continent travelers.\n\n**Pricing:** Highly competitive. Europe plans from $4.50 for 1GB, USA from $3.50, Japan from $4.50. Regional and global plans offer significant savings over single-country plans when visiting multiple destinations.\n\n**Network quality:** Connects to tier-1 local carriers in each country for maximum speed and reliability. 4G LTE standard, 5G available in supported areas.\n\n**Support:** 24/7 live chat support available directly from your dashboard.\n\n**Ease of use:** Buy online, receive QR code by email in seconds, scan and go. The entire process takes under 5 minutes.` },
      { h: 'Tips for Getting the Most from Your Travel eSIM', body: `**Buy before you fly:** Purchase and install your eSIM before departure. This way you\'re connected the moment you land, without needing Wi-Fi to set up the plan.\n\n**Enable data roaming:** After installing the eSIM, go to your phone settings and enable data roaming for the WoWo SIM profile. This is different from enabling roaming on your home SIM — it allows the eSIM to use local networks.\n\n**Set WoWo SIM as default data line:** In Settings → Mobile Data (iPhone) or Settings → Network & Internet (Android), set your WoWo SIM profile as the primary data line.\n\n**Keep your home SIM for calls:** Keep your home carrier SIM active for incoming calls from family, banking OTP messages, and other uses that require your original phone number.\n\n**Monitor data usage:** Check your data balance in phone settings to avoid running out at inconvenient moments. Buy a new plan proactively rather than waiting to run out.` },
